courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students are expected to achieve the following knowledge, skill, and attitude outcomes:
1. Knowledge:
• understand the many facets of the global hospitality and tourism industry;
• build a working knowledge of industry-specific terminology and management practices;
• understand the terms, issues and topics in commercial real estate;
• understand the complexities and challenges that face industry managers in today’s dynamic environment; and
• describe the career opportunities available in the industry.

2. Skills:
• identify the different product offerings and market segments, key trends and issues impacting the management practices used in the global hospitality and tourism industry;
• describe and interpret information and data relevant to the global hospitality, tourism, and real estate industries;
• describe the real estate development process;
• demonstrate effective communication and presentation skills;
• work effectively independently and with others both in classroom discussions and in practical learning; and
• self-appraise and reflect on practice.

3. Attitudes:
• develop an appreciation for service excellence and a positive service orientation;
• respect for human dignity and the environment;
• develop a global outlook and social awareness;
• develop an awareness of the fundamental ethics principles; and
• acknowledge and follow the Global Code of Ethics for Tourism as promoted by the United Nations World Tourism Organization (UNWTO).

Students are expected to achieve the following learning outcomes via participating in international experiences:
• Develop a stronger cross-cultural sensitivity and a global perspective;
• Gain experience of communicating and collaborating with students and/or other stakeholders abroad;
• Improve teamwork and problem-solving skills;
• Increase leadership confidence and competency;
• Improve abilities to reflect on personal experiences.

