This course is designed to develop or refine students:
1. Knowledge of the generally accepted principles and procedures of food and beverage management;
2. Knowledge of how to determine restaurant concepts, menu design, prepare labor staffing guides, work schedules and facility layouts;
3. Knowledge of service management and tools used to measure customer satisfaction, use of the menu as a control and a marketing tool; and
4. Ability to apply control procedures to the purchasing, receiving, and storage activities.

