courses.course_syllabus:
Course Objectives
At the conclusion of this course, you are expected to:

1. understand the three major perspectives on strategic management (traditional, resource-based view, and stakeholder management approach) and their applications in hospitality businesses;

2. be able to identify critical elements of a hospitality organization’s external environment and its internal resource base;

3. understand generic business and corporate strategies and how to choose appropriate strategy(ies) that meet environmental requirements and match organizational resources / capabilities;

4. know how to handle critical issues hospitality organizations may encounter in the process of implementing a chosen strategy; and

5. understand how entrepreneurship / innovation and the globalization trends affect hospitality firms’ survival and growth opportunities.

courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of this course, students should be able to:
