• Understand the nature of return and risk quantification and characteristics of property development and investment appraisals;
• Understand the theory and mechanics of financial feasibility studies in the property development process and know the strengths and weaknesses of development appraisals;
• Demonstrate capability to construct financial models using Microsoft Excel and/or ARGUS to do risk/return analysis and determine property value and income before they enter the workplace;
• Develop creative thinking, self-managed ability, leadership skills, team work spirit, analytical and communicative skills and oral presentation skills that are appropriate in a variety of investment scenarios through case studies and group projects;
• Understand and apply the knowledge of property investment and development analysis skills to real world practices and deliver excellent services to potential clients;
• Identify and address ethical issues in both real estate investment and development processes.

On completion of the course, students will be able to:

* understand the challenges/problems in traditional real estate practices;
* understand how PropTech solutions are used to solve these problems in different stages of the real estate process;
* learn to evaluate the benefits and potential risks of major PropTech applications;
* develop critical thinking and problem-solving skills;
* improve teamwork and communication skills.

